  "text": "A growing body of empirical work has documented contradictory results. [CITATION_1] construct an index of regulatory governance and find that it has a significant positive effects on their index of financial system soundness. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] find that supervisory independence is not related to bank development or efficiency or the level of non-performing loans. The theoretical model in this paper implies a specific empirical model to test the causal effect of supervisory arrangements on the riskiness of the banking sector. Moreover, it also allows the quantification of this effect, and the uncovering of the key components of a supervisory arrangement for effective banking supervision.",
